An 1858 ship of clipper construction named ''Memnon'', somewhat less heavily sparred, was built by E.H. & O Briggs in [[South Boston]]. She sailed from Boston under Captain Perez Jenkins on Aug. 30, 1858 arriving in San Francisco on Jan. 18, after a voyage of 159 days.<ref name="cutler2"/>

